**Naming Evaluation (First Priority)**:
- `sumBasePremiums`: Clear — sums base premiums. Good.
- `applyFirstInsuranceSurcharge`: Clear — applies the 10% first-insurance surcharge. Good.
- `quotePremium`: Clear — quotes a premium. Good.
- `executeStep`: Clear — executes one step. Good.
- `BLOCK_PREMIUM`: Refers to the block-of-3-components discount price. Acceptable, though could be more specific.
- `COMPONENT_TYPES`: Clear set of component types.

Names look reasonable.

**Current Code Mass for `sumBasePremiums`**:
```typescript
const sumBasePremiums = (items: Item[]): number => {
  const components = items.filter((item) => COMPONENT_TYPES.has(item.type));
  const mainItems = items.filter((item) => !COMPONENT_TYPES.has(item.type));
  const mainSum = mainItems.reduce((sum, item) => sum + BASE_PREMIUM[item.type], 0);
  const componentSum =
    components.length === 3 ? BLOCK_PREMIUM : components.reduce((sum, item) => sum + BASE_PREMIUM[item.type], 0);
  return mainSum + componentSum;
};
```

